				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Was the pill RU-486? The "morning after" pill?
<br />

<br />
Nope. Plain old birth control pills. And pro-life groups are backing him.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1101040607-644153,00.html" target="_blank">http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1101040607-644153,00.html</a>
<br />

<br />
Meanwhile, the cover story of this month's Discover magazine (yeah, yeah -- it was free) is about "surprising new research" that "raises the possibility that the viability of life may be determined days, weeks, or even months before conception." (It's all in the egg, fellas. Sorry.)
<br />

<br />
Look, a slippery slope is one thing, but this is getting ridiculous.<br />_________________<br />Bangzoom
