				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I believe employers can and do discriminate on religion where that religion will specifically prevent the prospective employee from executing the job in question.  If they can't then that's stupid.
<br />

<br />
I have no problem with a pharmacist behaving this way as long as he made that stance clear to his employer during the interview process.  If an employer is willing to condone it then good for them, but I seriously doubt it would fly in most cases.
<br />

<br />
What should the state do?  Nothing in my opinion.
<br />

